TIER 1: FOUNDATION (master these first):
------------------------------------------------------------
Array Traversal (basic loops, index manipulation)
Two Pointers (opposite ends, same direction)
Sliding Window (fixed/variable size)
Hash Tables (frequency maps, lookups)
Binary Search (classic, rotated, peak finding)
Sorting Algorithms (merge, quick, heap)
------------------------------------------------------------
TIER 2: INTERMEDIATE SAUCE:
------------------------------------------------------------
Stack/Queue (monotonic stack, deque tricks)
Linked List (two pointer, reversal, cycle detection)
Trees (DFS, BFS, traversals)
Dynamic Programming (1D, 2D, memoization)
Greedy (interval scheduling, huffman vibes)
Heap/Priority Queue (top K, merge streams)
------------------------------------------------------------
TIER 3: ADVANCED WIZARDRY
------------------------------------------------------------
Graphs (topological sort, shortest path, union find)
Backtracking (permutations, combinations, sudoku)
Trie (prefix trees, word games)
Segment Trees/Fenwick Trees (range queries)
String Algorithms (KMP, rolling hash, manacher)
-----------------------------------------------------------
TIER 4: COMPETITIVE PROGRAMMING FLEX
-----------------------------------------------------------
Advanced DP (bitmask, digit, tree DP)
Network Flow (max flow, bipartite matching)
Heavy-Light Decomposition
Suffix Arrays/Trees
